GOAL:
- Implement MFC-based swimlane timeline UI to visualize VSS activity.
- Lanes: Requester processes, vssvc.exe, volsnap, writers.
- Visualize both point events and span events.
- Enable selection and inspection of events/transactions.

CONSTRAINTS:
- Use MFC only (no WPF/Qt).
- Core (VssMon.Core) must not depend on UI.
- All GDI objects must be managed with RAII.
- Follow Google C++ style and C++ Core Guidelines.

UI_SPEC:
- Timeline is a custom CWnd-derived control.
- Time flows left â†’ right with adaptive zoom.
- Lane headers on the left show process name + PID if available.
- Point event = filled circle.
- Span event = filled rectangle.
- Selected item highlighted; hover shows tooltip.

INTERACTION:
- Mouse wheel: zoom in/out.
- Mouse drag: horizontal pan.
- Click: select event and notify main frame.

THREADING:
- Core emits events on worker thread.
- UI updates via PostMessage (no direct cross-thread calls).

